    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Who Invited the Bears?'' (Op-Ed, June 10):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Who Invited the Bears?'' (Op-Ed, June 10):</p>
        <p>Stephen Budiansky says ''coexistence must mean more than simply standing by as bears, deer and other species do as they please.'' It is sad that he and other ''wildlife management'' advocates fail to call for human beings to stop doing as they please -- irresponsibly reproducing and sprawling out their own habitats, thereby causing the destruction of animal habitats.</p>
        <p>Does coexistence mean that we keep slaughtering these creatures because there is no longer any room for them?</p>
        <p>BARBARA JOHNSTONE  Princeton, N.J., June 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
